Application: GQI, NGOD, video CLI
- Define its own video session data structures
- Maintain its own session database, using the DB utilities
- Implement application logic

SCM: 
- For coordination cross video applications
- For session info checking (to avoid collision, etc)
- Manage
  - Session ID usage
  - DestIP / UDP usage
  - QAM/prog number usage
  - QAM bandwidth

LCM:
- For corrdination of resource sharing between DEPI and video applications
  (e.g. QAM parameter provisioning, QAM modes setting)
- For LC communication


Coordination between modules:

E.g. GQI VOD session setup
- GQI allocate a data structure to store the session info
- GQI try to register the session's Dest IP/UDP, QAM, prog number,
  and bandwidth, etc with SCM.  In case of error, GQI will need to
  unregister fields that have already registered.
- GQI generate the input/output video session create messages
  and send them to the LC using the LCM API
- GQI stores the returned input/output session ID into its data structure,
- GQI registers the input/output session ID with SCM.
- GQI put the struture into its session DB with GQI session ID as a key,
  using the DB utilities.

- In case the source condition change, like input source becomes idle,
  LCM will receive a notification from LC
- LCM use the input session ID to query SCM for the corresponding application
- GQI receive the notice from LCM
- GQI uses the input session ID to retrieve the video session data structure
  from its session data base
- GQI check to see if additional source is available
- GQI update SCM for the new input source (SCM will verify the input also)
- GQI generate the input update message and send it to the LC thru the LCM


E.g.: GQI shell session setup
- GQI allocate group data structure for the shell create command
- GQI register the bandwidht requirement with SCM (SCM will also do checking)

